    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras are positioned for a high-ceiling offensive output today, led by **Yordan Alvarez** (78.41) and **Trea Turner** (69.16). **Yordan Alvarez** presents the safest path to production against the vulnerable Cecconi, whose 4.19 xERA offers a premium environment for elite xwOBA metrics. Meanwhile, **Trea Turner** remains the cornerstone of our strategy; despite facing a marginal hurdle from Rea\u2019s hold percentage, his leadoff spot and speed-based upside against a mediocre starter make him an auto-start. We are also monitoring **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (61.34), who benefits from a significant 14% platoon edge that offsets the difficulty of Nola\u2019s defensive peripherals, keeping him in the mix as a high-upside play.\n\nWe remain disciplined regarding our depth, as evidenced by the difficult benching of **Dillon Dingler** (36.01). While **Dillon Dingler** projected well in park factors, the combination of a tough matchup against Sonny Gray and an unfavorable platoon split ultimately pushed him below our 40.0 floor for the daily cap. We continue to manage our resources cautiously, keeping **Hyeseong Kim**, **Christian Yelich**, and **Zac Veen** off the active card due to injury, rest, or minor league status. With **Kazuma Okamoto** and **Colt Keith** providing steady, if unspectacular, value in the heart of the order, the roster is balanced to leverage high-efficiency matchups while mitigating exposure to elite arms like Detmers.",
